# Phantom-drift kill fixture (linear tc; tc_double_derive program). Batch 2
# is MD 5.1.1's batch (-edge(1,2), +edge(2,5)); the phantom join instance
# (X=2,From=1,To=5) transiently crosses zero on the + seed section. Batch 3
# removes edge(4,5), t(1,5)'s only real support -- t(1,5) must die.
# Truth: seeded t={(1,2),(1,4),(4,5),(1,5)}; final t={(1,4),(2,5)}.
batch
+ edge_msg 1 2
+ edge_msg 1 4
+ edge_msg 4 5
end
batch
- edge_msg 1 2
+ edge_msg 2 5
end
batch
- edge_msg 4 5
end
